<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 07 at 7:19AM EST  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...SPOTTY LIGHT FREEZING RAIN THIS MORNING...
A mixture of light rain, freezing rain, and sleet will affect
locations along and northwest of the Interstate 85 corridor from
Spartanburg to Gaffney to Charlotte this morning. While road
temperatures remain fairly warm, air temperatures hovering in the
lower 30s may create light icing in spots, especially on elevated
surfaces.
Allow extra travel time and stopping distance if driving this
morning. Be especially alert for any icing conditions on bridges
and overpasses.</description>
